text: William George Cameron (September 25, 1853 – October 29, 1930) was a Canadian politician. He served in the Legislative Assembly of British Columbia from 1903 to 1907 from the electoral district of Victoria City, as a Liberal. ==References== Category:British Columbia Liberal Party MLAs Category:People from Calaveras County, California Category:Politicians from Victoria, British Columbia Category:American emigrants to Canada Category:1853 births Category:1930 deaths
